articles.description: Rui Hachimura scored 23 points and No. 12 Gonzaga kept the ball out of Jock Landale's hands to end the nation's longest active winning streak at 19 games with a 78-65 victory over No. 11 Saint Mary's on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Gonzaga snaps Saint Mary's 19-game win streak, 78-65

images.caption: Zach Norvell Jr. lobs the ball up to Johnathan Williams who throws down a two-handed jam early in the first half.
images.name: Gonzaga's Norvell, Williams connect for alley-oop slam

articles.description: Evan Leonard scored 18 points and Tommy Rutherford scored 15 and UC Irvine beat UC Riverside 62-52 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: UC Irvine downs UC Riverside 62-52 behind Leonard's 18 PTs

articles.description: Michael Oguine had 25 points, including a crucial putback dunk in overtime, and Montana avoided an upset on Saturday night with a 71-69 win over Sacramento State.
articles.headline: Montana avoids upset, beats Sacramento State 71-69 in OT

articles.description: Deon Lyle came off the bench to hit 5 of 8 from 3-point range and score 18 and Giovanni De Nicolao added 10 points, including two free throws with five seconds left, to help UT San Antonio hold off UTEP 63-59 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: UT San Antonio holds off UTEP 63-59
